# Keep ONLY canonical attestation files and sprint summaries; ignore everything else.
# 
# CI validator reads: attestation.json, attestation-latest.json per task
# Dashboard reads: _summary.json per sprint

# Ignore non-attestation subdirectories entirely
sprint-*/execution/
sprint-*/planning/
sprint-*/reports/
sprint-*/specifications/
sprint-*/context/
sprint-*/follow-ups/
sprint-*/proposals/

# Inside attestations/: ignore everything inside task dirs, then whitelist canonical files
sprint-*/attestations/**
!sprint-*/attestations/*/
!sprint-*/attestations/*/attestation.json
!sprint-*/attestations/*/attestation-latest.json
# ADR-067 Phase 2: task-tracking.json is the canonical home for per-task OPERATIONAL +
# EVIDENCE content (status_history, blockers, execution.*, timings, kpis.actual/met, ...).
# It is tracked so the derived metrics tree can be regenerated from CSV + attestation + this.
!sprint-*/attestations/*/task-tracking.json
